author: @jxnhxi610
text: Today marks 3 years after the release of this music video, and I want to appreciate how hard Jun has worked to produce this MV, how much effort he pours into everything he does, and how far he has come. He started with an acting career for commercials and dramas as a shockingly young age. He later flew to Korea to train to become a Kpop idol, being unfamiliar with the environment, since he grew up in China. This was a very hard decision for him, since he also had the option of pursuing acting as his main career. Now, he's a very successful Kpop artist, receiving the Breakthrough Star of the Year at the 2023 Tencent White Paper Awards as a soloist, and SEVENTEEN as a group receiving the prestigious award of the Album of The Year Daesang at the 2023 MAMA Awards, as well. He has also continued his acting career recently, with the release of his new drama "Exclusive Fairytale" in July 2023. Keep in mind that having an acting career, as well as a career as an idol, is extremely time consuming and tiring because of busy schedules. Please also appreciate Jun's solos he has poured his time and efforts into, his digital singles being Crow, Silent Boarding Gate (this MV), Limbo, and Psycho, just to mention some of his releases. He's really such a beautiful person inside and out, and please keep supporting him and Seventeen, by streaming solos and group releases. Jun, please stay healthy, don't overwork yourself, and remember to stay happy. Remember that you've transformed many lives and pulled many out of dark moments in their lives, and some of us wouldn't be here without you. Love you, Jun.

author: @amiraxcle
text:
I loved this song when it was first released. When I heard it again after a while, I searched for the meaning behind the lyrics and cried. A lot.
 
"At the boarding gate 
I don't know where to go, I'm the one who can't let go 
There's a path but I don't have the heart to take it 
How long does it take for someone to say "I'm better now"  

I recently lost my beloved pet and the lyrics perfectly describe my feelings. I know I need to move on, but I can't let go. I don't think I ever will.

author: @chl0beary
text:
The dark clouds silently fade out
The love I didn't say then
You're the departure, I'm the future

After a few years of 'bad'
My heart suddenly felt better
You're not here

At the silent boarding gate
I saw the clouds flying away, the half orange half grey sky
Wanting to fly towards the next me
Shivering in the cold, I tighten my collar, unable to land
Our timelines not keeping in touch

At the boarding gate
I don't know where to go, I'm the one who can't let go
There's a path but I don't have the heart to take it
How long does it take for someone to say "I'm better now"

Guess how it turns out afterwards
The loneliness ignited the long-awaited disaster
I reap what I sow

At the silent boarding gate
I saw the clouds not moving, half conscious I surrendered
The one waiting to board wasn't me after all
Tears in my heart, I know that even after I land
Our timelines are in parallel

At the boarding gate
I don't know where to go, I'm the one who can't let go
There's a path but I don't have the heart to take it
How long does it take for someone to say "I'm better now"

author: @如莱卡
text:
I met a man. He is good, handsome, kind, brave, goofy, crybaby, genius, talented, lame, classic, fragrant, and lovely. I love him too much, and he loves me too much too. We both are so deeply in love. Promised to be with each other till we get married, have children, and grow old together. At first, we were both just trying it out, trying to love, trying to like someone more than friends. Both of us are hopeless romantics, never been in love before and had zero thought on getting married and live with one person for a whole lifetime. Yet, God had led us to meet and now we are so deeply in love and doesn't want to spend one day without each other. I want to engrave this memory, this love story here. So that one day when I come back here, I can read this all over again and remember the feeling of loving someone, being loved by someone, and in love.
- 13 Feb 2023
always loving you my prince.

author: @charriesayao5568
text: I want to escape. I want to quit. I want to end this. I always wonder why I hate my job, its not the job that I hate. It is the people around me. I am too scared to face them and it suffocates me just by interacting with them. The trauma that my family caused me is still lingering around me and it always triggering me everytime peope looking at me. What am I gonna do with my life? I lose my jon my family hates me. I have no friends, I have no reasons to move forward. I am thankful that I was able to meet you guys espcially you Jun, you're my emotional support but until when? I'm too tired.

author: @may.menesesc
text:
Hace poco más de un mes comencé a escuchar la música de Seventeen y por cosas de la vida decidí stanearlos y escogí a Jun como bias. Hace unos días me enteré de su solo y la verdad es que no dejo de escucharlo. Es increíble la capacidad que tiene la voz de Jun que puede reconfortarme y calmarme cuando más lo necesito. Esta canción y su voz, se volvieron mi lugar seguro. 
Gracias Jun por esta obra que nos has regalado, espero sigas entregándonos más de ti y de tus creaciones. 
Sin duda seguiré aquí para apoyarte a ti, como a Seventeen.
Te quiero <3

text:
THIS SONG IS SO BEAUTIFUL. I can't help but get emotional every time I listen to this and watch the MV. 

(English Translated Lyrics)
The dark clouds silently fade out
The love I didn't say then
You're the departure, I'm the future

After a few years of 'bad'
My heart suddenly felt better
You're not here

At the silent boarding gate
I saw the clouds flying away, the half orange half grey sky
Wanting to fly towards the next me
Shivering in the cold, I tighten my collar, unable to land
Our timelines not keeping in touch

At the boarding gate
I don't know where to go, I'm the one who can't let go
There's a path but I don't have the heart to take it
How long does it take for someone to say "I'm better now"

Guess how it turns out afterwards
The loneliness ignited the long-awaited disaster
I reap what I sow

At the silent boarding gate
I saw the clouds not moving, half conscious I surrendered
The one waiting to board wasn't me after all
Tears in my heart, I know that even after I land
Our timelines are in parallel

At the boarding gate
I don't know where to go, I'm the one who can't let go
There's a path but I don't have the heart to take it
How long does it take for someone to say "I'm better now"

so, jun's brother wrote a lovely letter...
in it he described how jun didn't care about his body before, kept doing martial arts on stages and hard iron floors, said it was gonna be okay, later on when he performed on one stage with hard flooring.... he hurt himself, multiple doctors didn't help him, finally he got a doctor who was genuine and kind, helped him get well and recover, finally jun was in a good state again.. his brother then described how proud and happy he was of his brother, how he looked up to him..
jun has suffered alot, he came to a country of which he didn't even know the language and found it very hard to communicate, I'd never want to stop supporting this boy... he's too good for us ❤️

English translation 

The dark clouds silently fade out
The love I didn't say then
You're the departure, I'm the future

author: @adeen836
text: The kind of song you’d never get bored of ;-; it’s so pretty, I cry to this everyday. I cry knowing life will never be perfect. I cry remembering my two best friends I left on the other side of the Earth and write letters to. I cry over everyone and everything I’ve had to lose. This song perfectly encapsulates my feelings for every single thing in my life. I listen to this before bed to have good dreams too. I want to have good dreams because those are the only source of good reality left for me... the world holds nothing I can hope for anymore. I like my alternate imaginative universe, just me with my cat, in a car watching the stars up above without a care in the universe. I just wish the universe was what we wanted it to be.

author: @samahsultan3690
text: I'm actually disappointed about how carats and casual fans just sleep on Jun, this bundle of talent, kindness, a genius, a skillful dancer and an ethereal vocalist? It makes me sad to think that Gose's episodes will get 600k vi3ws in a day, or that the most popular MV's are being str3amed all right, but not Jun's first solo MV. It's unacceptable that he gets the least recognition in his work out of all the members, and yet works as hard. I'm not a huihui, but an OT13, and yet I feel that Jun still deserves so much better, especially in Korea and internationally (not just China). I wish that Pledis would promote him properly and that more carats give him the love and support he deserves. I know popularity is not measured by vi3ws, but they are still important.

author: @iwish89
text:
everytime i watch silent boarding gate, i feel like watching a movie. junhui and the actress's acting, the scenery, video editing, a whole MV was so perfect and I never get bored by watch it all the time. every scenes of junhui stares the actress never fail to make me smiling, and give me a feel of flutter. you can feel the warmth between them when they were still together. and after the compilation of the scenes when they were together, I can exactly feel the sadness and emptiness by looking at junhui being alone at the end. 

junhui is really great actor, i never get boring to give him appreciation about how great he act. he exactly have a different side here. one side are happy and the other side are sad. his expression, gaze, was really no joke. i'm so in love with this precious human being, i hope he will get a chance to act again, as he wish all the time.

author: @caratako8270
text:
文俊辉 (JUN)(SEVENTEEN) – 寂寞号登机口 (Silent Boarding Gate)(English Translation)
 Lyrics: 
     Overcast clouds blur wordlessly
      The love I never verbalized at    
                     that time
     You are departure, I am the future

        Experiencing a few bad years 
        My heart suddenly became well 
                    You’re not here 
   At the boarding gate of loneliness
   I watch the clouds fly away, a sky     
                      half grey
                     half orange
        I want to fly to the next me
             It’s so cold I shiver,
            I hold my collar close, 
                   unable to land 
   Two places of time and space that 
                        do not      
                  communicate

             At the boarding gate 
      Where I decide to go – it is me in  
                    half memory,
              half forgottenness
    There’s a path but not the mind to     
                       walk it 
    How long until someone can say:
                 ‘I’m okay now’? 

        Guess what happened later 
   Loneliness sparked a disaster that    
  I had not seen again for a long time 
               It’s what I deserve...

   At the boarding gate for loneliness, 
    I see the clouds have not left, in  
                    half-dream      
                     half-wake, 
                    I surrender
     It is not me that is waiting to fly 
        The tears are in the heart, 
             I know that later 
                even if I land 
  Two places of space and time in    
                     parallel
 
           At the boarding gate
 Where I decide to go – it is me in     
                 half memory,
            half forgottenness
    There’s a path but not the mind to    
                       walk it 
  How long until someone can say:   
                ‘I’m okay now’?

 Credits to: @gyuaena...

text:
The dark clouds silently fade out
The love I didn't say then
You're the departure, I'm the future

After a few years of 'bad'
My heart suddenly felt better
You're not here

At the silent boarding gate
I saw the clouds flying away, the half orange half grey sky
Wanting to fly towards the next me
Shivering in the cold, I tighten my collar, unable to land
Our timelines not keeping in touch

At the boarding gate
I don't know where to go, I'm the one who can't let go
There's a path but I don't have the heart to take it
How long does it take for someone to say "I'm better now"

Guess how it turns out afterwards
The loneliness ignited the long-awaited disaster
I reap what I sow

At the silent boarding gate
I saw the clouds not moving, half conscious I surrendered
The one waiting to board wasn't me after all
Tears in my heart, I know that even after I land
Our timelines are in parallel

author: @nics.x2747
text:
FOR THOSE WORRIED ABOUT THE NUM. OF VI3WS: 
- FIRST, YT views don’t really mean much for a Chinese song/MV since YT is banned in China so basically, the success of the song isn’t based on that. Which also means to say, most of the viewers who actually streamed this masterpiece listened to the song not because we understand any of it, but because it’s A FRKN MASTERPIECE. 
- SECOND, here’s an article made about JUN’s solo album and i’ll leave it to ya (source: KpopStarz, KoreaBoo) 

“The Billboard World Digital Song Sales chart ranks 25 digital singles by artists around the world who have the most sales in the world music genre in a certain week. And for the week ending on Feb. 20, SEVENTEEN Jun is among the K-pop artists who made it to the list.

On Feb. 5, the "Adore U" singer launched a new solo track titled "Crow," which serves as a pre-release song for his solo album "Silent Boarding Gate" that came out on Feb. 14. Shortly after SEVENTEEN Jun's new solo track came out, it quickly rose to the top of the iTunes Song chart in five countries and secured spots in the chart's top 10 in eight different regions.

And now, SEVENTEEN Jun's new song has debuted on the Billboard chart, claiming the No. 14 position. The male idol now earns a Billboard spot alongside K-pop's biggest acts such as PSY, IU, BTS, BLACKPINK, and more.

*OUR BOY MADE IT. THE VI3WS DIDN’T MATTER.* 

The target audience was China, yet it reached Global success. With that said, let’s not compare the members’ solo projects and instead show our support to all of them! 
Seranghaaaeee

author: @eckamirceb7729
text:
it’s 3 AM and you’re at the airport. since travel restrictions got tighter you know the place was going to be pretty quiet; nevertheless you book an early flight just to be safe. no one coming, no one going. you stare out the window at the pre-dawn morning, realizing this ungodly hour has brought you closer to heavenly peace than you thought possible. no one’s coming, no one’s going. they won’t stop you, but maybe they should? you will get there, but maybe won’t? maybe it will be better to stay, where you know you’ll be safe, where you know what will happen. or maybe you can take this chance. maybe you can go farther than you ever thought you could, than they ever believed you could. 
it is silent at the boarding gate. no one to send you off, no one to greet you where you arrive. you’re scared but you’re calm; you’re sure but you’re not. the only thing you are certain of is that once you step on that plane, everything changes.
but that’s the point, is it not?

author: @Kathu17
text:
Por favor no piensen que por las pocas visitas Jun no ha tenido éxito en su solo. Las vistas de YT no definen el éxito de ningún artista, Jun lo ha hecho demasiado bien en China siendo su mercado principal.

Se posicionó #1 en plataformas Chinas como QQ Music, ahora SBG junto con Crow tienen casi 5M de reproducciones, rompió récords en plataformas Chinas, y hablando del extranjero, superó a Home;Run en iTunes con la posición más alta que ha tenido el grupo y lo hizo él solo, ahora incluso en varios países sigue estando en una posición elevada a pesar de que ya fue más de un mes.

Sigamos apoyando a Jun y hagamos str3am, pero por favor dejen de hablar de su solo como si la gente no le hubiera prestado atención ¡porque es lo contrario! Y recuerden no comparar los proyectos de los chicos 💓

The dark clouds silently fade out

Our timelines not keeping in touch

I reap what I sow

author: @vrnfn9944
text:
Prompt I made inspired by this mv : 

“You have me, until every last star in the galaxy dies, you have me.” Junhui whispered into his lovers ears as they watch the lantern drift away in the beautiful night sky. Their hands intertwined and they felt comfortable wrapped around each other’s arms.

Little did he know that the lantern wasn’t the only one who would drift away, his lover did too. She whispered to him in his dream “You have me, until every last star in the galaxy dies, you have me.” 

I saw a writing challenge in twt where we have to use the first line of the prompt as the last line too but with a different tone/energy. So I did it and this is inspired by this lovely mv <3

author: @latteyo2259
text:
I can’t get over this song, and I’ll never stop being so proud of Jun T^T

I read somewhere that he was glad he got scouted as an idol because he was having a slump with his acting career/didn’t know what to do. I might be wrong, but anyways... Through that, he managed to become an idol in a talented, amazing, out-of-the-world 13-membered group called SEVENTEEN. And there, he found 12 other new brothers, a family he can carry on his journey with, and he won’t be alone for sure. Now, with this song, this solo album, he’s shining brightly and will continue to shine even brighter in the future.

I really love his voice and this song, along with Crow! I hope that the other members will one day release their own solo albums too \(≧∇≦)/ Until then, I’ll do my best to support this all I can first! Hwaiting, Carats!

author: @hochistrm6006
text:
wowow I got inspired so I wrote a little something :: 

the time ticks on, slower and slower. grey and orange hues paint the sky, and the man waits in front of the large window. in his hand, he grasps firmly his briefcase— all his woes and joys. the light flickers to green. a longing look brushes across the area, and he takes a step forward. when he is gone, this will only be a place to reminisce about; but is that what would really happen? ..soft whirring starts as the gate closes. he disappears, leaving behind only the faintest of memories. 
to abandon the current and move on to the next— it is said that the timelines only connect as you wait in the Silent Boarding Gate . 

but, for the first time, he stops to think; even if he has been to this Gate thousands of times— he still comes back. perhaps, he knows what will happen next as he travels to the next. at this moment, the man realises: he isn't the one who's waiting to fly. 
maybe, this Silent Boarding Gate doesn't only take you to another timeline. maybe, it helps you heal. and the man realises this too, as the scenery around him dissolves into a city district. in his half dreaming state, he barely recognises this place. he awaits— for a familiar beckoning. one he has heard as much as he has boarded the Gate— 

"Hey, Junhui!" a cheerful voice calls from behind him. he turns around . what greets him are twelve boys, shining as bright as  diamonds in the light. 

at that moment, he makes a decision— this will be the last time this scene replays itself, the last time he meets these boys, the last time he steps onto the Silent Boarding Gate. this will be the last timeline he travels to, and the moment these boys leave him— it will end. he promises himself; no more heartbreak. no more foolishness. 

his heart swells. this is his last, and _forever._

author: @최선주-i2p
text:
*1절

乌云无语晕开 当时没说的爱 你是离开我是未来
먹구름이 말 없이 번져가요
그 때 전하지 못한 사랑은
당신은 출발, 나는 연착

经历几年的坏 心也猛然好了起来 你不在
몇년의 아픔이 지나고
불쑥 마음도 좋아져 오지만
당신이 여기 없네요
​
在寂寞号登机口 我瞧云飞走 半橘半灰的天空 想飞往下一个我
여기 적막호 탑승구에서
흘러가는 구름, 귤색인듯 잿빛인듯한 하늘을 보고 있으니
다음 정류장의 내게로 날아가고 싶어집니다

冷的发抖 我拉紧领口 没法降落 两个时空不联络
몸서리치게 추워서
옷을 꼭 여미어 봤지만
착륙할 방법 없이
두 시공간은 이어지지 않네요

登机门口 我何去何从 半念半忘的是我 有路但没有心走 人得多久 能说 我好了
게이트 앞
나는 어디로 가야하나요
온전히 잊지 못한건 나에요
노선이 있어도 가는 마음들은 없어요
사람이라면 시간이 아무리 흘러도 말 할 수 있어야해요
‘나는 괜찮아’ 라고요

*2절

后来怎样 你猜 孤独引燃久违的灾 我活该
그 뒤에 어떻게 되었을까요.
한 번 맞춰보세요
긴 이별이라는 재앙에 고독이 불을 붙였어요
저는 그래도 싸요

在寂寞号登机口 我瞧云没走 半梦半醒我自首 等飞的并不是我
여기 적막호 탑승구에서
흐르지 않는 구름과, 꿈인듯 생시인듯한 나 자신을 보고있으니
비행기를 기다리는 것은 내가 아니네요

泪在心中 我知道之后 就算降落 两个时空平行中
눈물이 마음에 가득함을 알고
착륙을 포기하고나니
두 시공간이 평행해집니다
​
登机门口 我何去何从 半念半忘的是我 有路但没有心走
人得多久 能说 我好了
게이트 앞
나는 어디로 가야하나요
온전히 잊지 못한건 나에요
노선이 있어도 가는 마음들은 없어요
사람이라면 시간이 아무리 흘러도 말 할 수 있어야해요
‘나는 괜찮아’ 라고요

author: @celinedonguines574
text:
The dark clouds silently fade out
The love I didn't say then
You're the departure, I'm the future

After a few years of 'bad'
My heart suddenly felt better
You're not here

At the silent boarding gate
I saw the clouds flying away, the half orange half grey sky
Wanting to fly towards the next me
Shivering in the cold, I tighten my collar, unable to land
Our timelines not keeping in touch

At the boarding gate
I don't know where to go, I'm the one who can't let go
There's a path but I don't have the heart to take it
How long does it take for someone to say "I'm better now"

Guess how it turns out afterwards
The loneliness ignited the long-awaited disaster
I reap what I sow

At the silent boarding gate
I saw the clouds not moving, half conscious I surrendered
The one waiting to board wasn't me after all
Tears in my heart, I know that even after I land
Our timelines are in parallel
At the boarding gate
I don't know where to go, I'm the one who can't let go
There's a path but I don't have the heart to take it
How long does it take for someone to say "I'm better now"

😢

author: @Hoshimi315
text: Hello Junhui, you probably won't ever see this, but I want to thank you for this song. Ever since the release, this song has become two of my top comfort songs, the other one is Seungkwan's Love Poem cover. I know this song is supposed to be sad, but listening to your voice never fails to smooth all the tangled up knots in my mind. This is your most beautiful song, and I cannot thank you enough for giving this to us, to me, in these times where I need comfort the most. Thank you for always challenging yourself, releasing all these beautiful works that you poured your heart out for. It touched my heart to its deepest layers and lift all the weights inside of me. Thank you for this song, Jun. Thank you for being you.

author: @mays2877
text:
I usually don't cry when it comes to songs and there are only like 2 songs that made me cry. But this one got me burst into tears when I first heard it. I think it's the fact that Jun put all his soul and heart into it. It's such a beautiful song and I listen to it on repeat. I love the lyrics, the sound of it, Jun's voice... I just love it. I am not a real Carat to be honest - I catch up with the boys, but I don't even know all of their names (yet) and I don't listen to them that often. But I am begging everyone - Carat or not - to listen to this masterpiece and spread it everywhere because it deserves so much attention. Jun is such a good singer and person, and even though I don't consider myself a real Carat, I have to say that he is my bias in Seventeen (not only because of his talents). 

This is so beautiful and I am so in love with this.

author: @babyzee789
text:
[Jun little brother letter]
My Brave Brother

My elder brother really handsome. Under that naturally-born handsome face, with that pair of mischievous eyes, under those arched eyebrows, appears especially charming. Coupled with that prominent nose and that lip which is "just-right"- it's perfect! And with that slender figure, its pace is as light and graceful as the willows that blossom in spring. With the height of 1.8cm, he looks really dashing when he dances, thinking back to those days, the look on his face when he sings and that melodious voice, who knows how many hearts of those young girls he had captured? This is my elder brother Wen Jun Hui.

The elder brother that I had in my memory is the most outstanding, the strongest, I've been following and admired him. When my brother was in high school, there was a period that was unforgettable to me, at the same time, it was the most painful day for him too.

text:
[Translate by @BongbongieCarat on twitter]
Moon Junhui (25) Stage name: Jun Nationality. Chinese
Casting anecdote:
in a convenience store in Shenzen, China, he got casted while he was with his friends. He was already a child actor in China (his video still shows up in Shenzen's subway) but
He takes off his child actor image and because he wants to have a fresh start he came to Korea.
Thus, Pledis brought in a boy that was an actor and make him a singer (This is also an ability)
Of all things, his first day as a trainee was a performance test day, so after watching his members dance, his competitiveness is formed
October 2012 he joined as the 9th trainee. 25 December 2012 with the start of SEVENTEEN TV1 March 2013 2014 he came out on SEVENTEEN TV season 2,3,4,5 (18-19 years old)

author: @choo9953
text:
ENGLISH LYRICS

Overcast clouds blur wordlessly 
The love I never verbalized at that time
 You are departure, I am the future 

Experiencing a few bad years 
My heart suddenly became well 
You’re not here 

At the boarding gate of loneliness 
I watch the clouds fly away, a sky half grey half orange
 I want to fly to the next me 
It’s so cold I shiver, I hold my collar close, unable to land 
Two places of time and space that do not communicate 

At the boarding gate 
Where I decide to go – it is me in half memory, half forgottenness 
There’s a path but not the mind to walk it 
How long until someone can say: ‘I’m okay now’? 

Guess what happened later 
Loneliness sparked a disaster that I had not 
seen again for a long time 
It’s what I deserve

At the boarding gate for loneliness, 
I see the clouds have not left, in half-dream half-wake,
I surrender
It is not me that is waiting to fly 
The tears are in the heart, I know that later even if I land 
Two places of space and time in parallel 

At the boarding gate 
Where I decide to go – it is me in half memory, half forgottenness 
There’s a path but not the mind to walk it 
How long until someone can say: ‘I’m okay now’? 

Credits to: @gyuaena

author: @micahthelibra
text:
_storytime_
Jun was the reason why I met seventeen. He really caught my attention in the left&right era despite having a little screentime in their mv. Before, I never want to stan any other groups beside my old main stan (bts) however I met seventeen because of Jun. I slipped into the diamond life. I thought he was really cool main dancer (im a sucker for dancers) that have a boy next door aura of idol. However as I know them better, I saw how Jun was a shy and introvert member.  I never would have thought that the man in the center of hit, the center in the dance break of getting closer, and more was a very shy idol who was even criticized because of him being an expressionless in dancing on their 17 project. 

I am beyond proud than how far Jun has come. In their 17 project he even said that he write lyrics in Chinese and fast forward years later, he is releasing his own single. Him being great in dancing despite him not having trained for so long because his main forte is acting and him having the sweetest voice that calms me. Everything about Jun just makes me happy. Thank you very much for this song Jun! We will support you always! 묵랑해~

author: @leah8404
text:
- a long and sentimental post !!

Posting this long post, I just want to share the warmth that I personally felt from Jun's <Silent Boarding Gate>. 

Actually when I first heard the song, I didn't get too much of the song's highlights, I was just captured by Jun's gentle vocals. After looping it for two to three times, scenes that were really warm started appearing in my mind. 
When I listened to the prelude of the song again, it felt like you were walking alone on a path against the sunset, the setting sun is beautiful, life isn't too bad, although alone and lonely, all the chaos and happenings are unrelated to me.

"The dark clouds silently disperse" The love you had for another person is just like the dark clouds that disperse and spread in the skies, covering up the skies' original colors. It's like loving a person deeply but never expressing it. There's always a dark cloud in your heart, when you're prepared to eliminate this dark cloud, the other person chooses the present, while you only consider the future, both of you have no choice but to separate. Many years later, this became dull in your life, maybe you'd only think, the person who accompanied you while walking under the sunset has disappeared from your life. 

"At the Silent Boarding Gate" You want to escape this chaotic world, so you go to the boarding gate with your luggage. While waiting for the plane, you saw the sunset that shone through the window and onto the seats. You look up at the sky, half of it was enveloped by dark clouds, the other half was orange from the sunset. Maybe you had let go half, but you're unable to to completely let go of that situation in your heart. After boarding the plane, the plane slowly takes off, you plan to let go of the past you and fly towards a better you. But after all you're used to the world that you thought was chaotic, when trying to change yourself, you feel lonelier, even if the present you wish to stop, it's also too late. After all the you that you wish to become, and the past you, are in two different time spaces, how would there be a connection. 

Facing this boarding gate, you start having doubts on whether your thoughts were right. Half of it - missing the life you had with the other person, the other half of it has been forgotten, just like the half-orange and half-grey skies. There's a path clearly present, but you don't have the courage to walk on it. You then question, "How long would it take to be able to say, 'I'm okay'"

"Guess what happens after" Because I don't have you by my side, I feel that life is very lonely. From what I can tell, a life without you has already become a disaster. But thinking about it, it's because of your weakness then that caused you to lose the other person, you'd blame yourself, "I deserved it"

You're back at the boarding gate, and saw that half the clouds are still grey as always. At this moment, it's like you became clear-headed, but you don't want to accept this reality. However you understand, that leaving this chaotic world isn't really realistic. Even though there's tears in your heart, even though you have chosen to stop in your tracks, you're only able to stop in between the two time-spaces. 

In the future, maybe there are times during busy days where you'd feel alone and lonely, but once you stop in your steps that are walking towards the future, you will realize that you are really a person. Alone, lonely and overwhelming. You will feel overwhelmed with emotions, thinking how you'd walk towards a better future, how long would it take for you to be able to walk out of that situation. 

From my perspective, this song shows emotions of many graduates and young adults. There could be things that happened in the past that you regretted, which made you unsure of how to face the future, and you decide to start afresh after calmly considering and forgetting the past. But it seems like the past can never be wiped clean in your heart. In the process of working hard. there's a possibility that you will hit a plateau/periods that are difficult, hence there's a boarding gate. You have to look at your choice in your heart, to see if you're able to get rid of your past state of mind, and walk towards the future. You have to make your own choices for yourself, this process may be lonely, there may not be people who support your decisions and no one understands you, but you have to believe that there will definitely be a day where you'll be able to say "I'm okay".

No matter how you understand it, I hope that this song of Jun's will be able to warm everyone, and help everyone who are currently facing choices. As long as you follow your own heart, even though its a boarding gate to flight loneliness*, there will be a day where a plane will fly just for you. 

Lastly, from <Can You Sit By My Side> to <Silent Boarding Gate>, I can hear Jun's huge improvements. There were new improvements on his vocals that were already elegant. All in all, <Silent Boarding Gate> is perfect in my eyes.

author: @ashleyley2715
text:
After listening to this over and over again, I was surprised to find a motivation within me to actually understand the Chinese lyrics. Although I didn't even know how to write 寂寞号登机口, I decided to try to know each character in the lyrics and maybe translate it? 2 days later of more replays, here is my interpretation of the poetic lyrics. I wish I could describe how much I admire Jun for crafting this song but every listen just leaves me speechless all the time. 谢谢文俊辉! 你的唱歌很好听 :> CARAT想坐在你的身旁!

Dark clouds disperse without a word 
In time, love is left unspoken 
You are the departure and I am the return

After going through years of bad events, 
I find my heart has suddenly healed
You're not here 

At the silent boarding gate 
I look over the floating clouds, a half orange and half grey sky
I want to fly towards another me  
Shivering from the cold, I tighten my grip on my collar (but) I can't land
The two time-spaces are unable to come into contact 

The entrance of the boarding gate 
What path should I take? It's me who's half wanting to remember and half wanting to forget 
There's a path ahead but my heart can't take the step 
How long does it take for someone to be able to say, "I'm alright now"? 

Can you guess what happens next? 
Loneliness ignites into a long-gone disaster 
And I deserved it 

At the silent boarding gate
I look over the unmoving clouds; in my half dreaming and half awakening state, I surrender
But I'm not the one waiting to fly 
Tears are at the centre of my heart, I know that even if I land after this 
The two time-spaces will be parallel 

The entrance of the boarding gate 
What path should I take? It's me who's half wanting to remember and half wanting to forget 
There's a path ahead but my heart can't take the step
How long does it take for someone to be able to say, "I'm alright now"?

author: @hw4651
text:
So I decided to translate the lyrics to support our Jun and here's my work:

Dark clouds dissipate wordlessly
The love that were unspoken of back then
You are departure and I am future

After a few years of bad time
My heart suddenly lightens
You're not here

At the boarding gate of flight loneliness
I watch as the cloud fly away, the sky looks half grey and half orange
I want to fly to the next me
It's so cold I'm shivering, I pull my collar tight, and I‘m unable to land
Two different time and space and they don’t communicate

At the boarding gate
I don't know where to go, I remember some but forgot some
There is a path but I don't feel like going
How long does it take for one to say “I'm fine now”

And guess what comes after
The long coming diaster ignited by loneliness
I deserve it

At the boarding gate of flight loneliness
I see that the cloud stays, and I turn myself in not fully awake
It's not me who's waiting to fly
The tears are in my heart
I know that after, even if it lands
Two time and space will be parallel

At the boarding gate
I don't know where to go, I remember some but forgot some
There is a path but I don't feel like going
How long does it take for one to say “I'm fine now”


It's hard to decide on the tense and the right way to do it, because the lyrics are quite abstract. Anyway I hope that you enjoyed the song and my translation💕

author: @meowjun9374
text:
Whenever I think about it, it gives me the feeling of longing for something or someone. 
As we try to survive each day, we have to overcome every struggles, do decisions and even do some sacrifices, just to get what we dream of.

Sometimes, we just need to do some sacrifices, to leave things behind, even if it is really hard for us to let go about things just to achieve what we want to be.

The pain inside us, the tears we've hold back, the aches we've concealed, and everything..
We just need to be strong enough to cross the path, to move on, to stay alive, and to look on the brighter side, even if we just have to convince ourselves with the words "I'm fine" just to have some valor.

Trying to connect the past with the future. But sometimes, we do not need to dwell on the past. Sometimes, we just need to let go. But yeah, memories will always remain. We just need to comfort ourselves and as time passes by, we heal.

Truth hurts and reality bites.

But what we really have is our selves. Sometimes, we only need our selves to stand firm amidst all odds.

Life is too dramatic. Life is like a maze, we can be perplexed any time.

But I hope everyone of us will have his/her own HAPPINESS.

LIFE MIGHT KNOCK US DOWN, BUT WE NEED TO HAVE ENOUGH COURAGE TO STAND ALONE AND BE FIRM, BECAUSE WE ARE IN FULL CONTROL OF OURSELVES. WHATEVER MAY HAPPEN, LIFE MUST GO ON. SO WE MUST ALWAYS LOOK ON THE BRIGHTER SIDE.

life is short and tomorrow is not promised to anyone, anywhere. some people die in their sleep, i am telling this for us to realize that there really is an urgency for change of heart. i don't want anyone else to be in danger of losing their own soul just because no one told them about this. 

please let us all stop involving ourselves in magic, new age, chakras, divinations, spiritualism, witchcraft, law of attraction, astral projection,tarot, etc. these are all demonic. it brings good to you because it wants you to stay until your soul is already tied to it. it's wolves in sheep's clothing! 

if this life we have is temporary, there is eternal life waiting on the other side. same thing, if there is one death on earth then there's eternal death. it's either heaven or hell and it's real, no doubt, just look around and you'll see the difference. if we were to all die tonight where would you be after death?

there is no other way, Jesus is the only way. demons are real, satan is real, spiritual attacks are real, God is real!  the sufferings we experience are caused by evil and still, God brings the good out of it for us. 

 accept Jesus as your Lord and Savior now, that'll be the best decision you've ever madewe don't just live to die, Romans 6:23 "For the wages of sin is death, but the gift of God is eternal life in Christ Jesus our Lord." we die because all of us sinned and that's one enough reason why we need to get right with God. 

REPENT, we all sinned against GOD and after asking for forgiveness, we need to turn away from it. 

ACCEPT JESUS AS YOUR LORD AND SAVIOR, we all will die and all will be judged, JESUS died on the cross as wages for our sins and if we don't accept it, we will die for our own in the eternal lake of fire. 

BE BORN AGAIN, im not talking about religion, its about laying down your past self and making your identity and life new through and for JESUS. 

GOD loves us all and we must get right back with HIM. this world will perish, all people will die, but GOD is eternal and stop the doubt. believe to see!

 God bless you all, brothers and sisters! ❤️

author: @minimanimo7750
text:
so this is the theory:

jun already died and at the beginning of the mv, he is on his way walking to the afterlife (board) (on the thumbnail too). while he was walking he just reminiscing all the past happy memories they had together when he was alive. and at 1:02 of the mv when he looks back maybe he was waiting for her (the girl) to come with him but she didn't (the girl still alive). 

and that is why the lyrics mentioned: 
"two places of time and space that do not communicate" - (referring to the afterlife and the real world). 

"there's a path but not mind to walk it" - (path to afterlife that he didnt want to walk and left all the happy memories behind).

"at the boarding gate of loneliness" 
"it is me in half memories, half forgottenness" - (walking to afterlife while recall the memories that will fade away later). 💔

author: @carat9014
text:
So from my understanding of the Chinese lyrics is that in this song, the man lost his woman. '寂寞' also means lonely and lonesome in Chinese while '登机口' means boarding port, and so the translation could also be 'Lonely Boarding Port' because the guy feels lonely after having lost the woman that he loves. There is a part '两个时空不联络' (pinyin: liăng gè shí (kong(first sound))bù lián luò)These two worlds/universe don't connect' but the direct translation of the word '时空' would be 'time space' in English, but I translated to world/universe, as in 'parallel universe'. Another verse similar to this is '两个时空平行中 (pinyin: liăng gè shí (kong(first sound)) píng xíng (zhong(first sound)) which is translated to 'the two worlds/universes are parallel(verb, not noun)'. '平行中' directly translated could be 'paralleling' (present tense, verb)
Sorry for the short translation but I hoped this helped in the very least! I apologize for any mistakes in here and feel free to correct me by replying to this comment here!

author: @cline454
text: Junhui sometimes looks at the girl and like shrugs it of as if he knows she's not real, she's not with him.. I think she's a figment of his imaginations, on the first scene the girl sat down, but in the end there's no chair. He looks at her and shrugs it of when they were walking as he guides her. The light, it was only on him at the last part therefore he was just really alone...  the bed, it seems untouched..  lastly the lantern scene..  the girl lifts the lantern higher than him as if she was air and not holding it with him.. It's just what i observe after watching it multiple times

author: @babyzee789
text:
Wen Junhui (Chinese: 文俊辉; Korean: 문준휘; born 10 June 1996), also known by his stage name Jun (Korean: 준), is a Chinese singer and actor based in South Korea. He is a member of the South Korean boy group SEVENTEEN and its sub-unit "Performance Team" under Pledis Entertainment.

Before joining SEVENTEEN, He was a child actor who starred in multiple films including The Pye Dog (2006), for which he won the Hong Kong Film Directors' Guild's Best New Actor Silver Award. In 2010, he played the young Ip Man in The Legend Is Born: Ip Man.

author: @ginag.5579
text:
To people passing by who is always curious in chinese music and actually loves this song, he is Wen Junhui, Seventeen's performance unit who has a heavenly voice , JUN. Jun's from Shenzhen, China and have trained as a kpop idol under Pledis ent. since October 2012. He worked really hard as a trainee for 3 years to finally debut in Seventeen with 12 other members. 

Also did you know? Jun was a child actor and if you knew The Legend Is Born: Ip Man (2010), well this man actually acted in it as the young ip man. Junhui have a very kind soul that you can make a whole article about his kindness to Seventeen, his fans and especially his Family. He sacrificed so much to not add any burden to his mother and cared for his little brother so much ( even I as the oldest in the family feels tired with this responsibility and felt like giving up so many time)

So did you know? Wen Junhui is my role model to become the best of me. Now to rant about this song.... there's so much, seriously. I lost so much in this life. Some left me so they could move on with their own life, some really did left this world to go to a better place. And as I mention before, I'm the oldest in the family but logically, I am not. My mom had a miscarriage twice before she had me. Carats ( our fandom ) made a theory that the girl in the Mv is actually Jun's imagination, a person that is not real, and that HITS because I imagined my life with them since I was 5 or something.  While this song pains me, it also acts as some sort of comfort to my messed up emotions.


If you liked Silent Boarding Gate, he also released a song "Crow" and you can easily find it on spotify or any other streaming sites. My fav quote in the song is "My heart is shattered, I face it calmly, honesty is depressing" and "Crows in the world are black But they are not heartless"

Okay wow I talked a lot but anyways, have a great day :)

If we can reach 3-6 Million views for group MVs and 300K-600K gose episodes in a day, I hope we can all show our support to Jun's music. He released a lot of songs and finally filmed this alone. Jun is an introvert and not that super confident with his talent and capabilities, he tries to hide it by being quiet or sometimes by joking, but we know for sure that the results of his compositions/work matters to him and to his members. BUT Now that he is giving us his full potential, (AND I SWEAR THIS SONG AND HIS OTHER WORKS ARE SUCH A MASTERPIECE), I hope we can all fully support him and give him the best results that he deserves!! author: @christinesong8472
text:
Jun can be super quirky which makes his actions and words so spontaneous and funny. In the fandom, we joke how random, sometimes adorably awkward, and precious he is. But he also has this incredibly serious and hardworking side to him. We’ve seen how logical he can be during debate nights and calm in difficult situations. Obviously I’ve never met him but he seems diligent, absolutely patient, and loving, and I think you can sense those attributes in this song. He put in a lot of thought, work, and sincerity like Seventeen does with all their songs. And so this song definitely calmed and touched my heart. 

I don’t know a speck of what he’s saying but I can sense some sort of longing mixed in with a bit of regret and nostalgia. Like wanting to move forward but it’s hard

author: @shin4839
text:
After watching this. I made a one shot 

--

Junhui went to a coffee shop with his sketchbook. The atmosphere of the coffee shop was relaxing, he sat on the empty chair and start to drew.

He smiled as he allign the girl face on the paper. The girl he was currently making/draw was the girl appeared on his dream.

While he was busy, a girl knocked on his table. He startled and look at the girl and he even got more startled when he familiarized the girl. It was the girl in his dream.

The girl sat beside him and out of nowhere, she grabbed a pen and start to draw a moon with a star on his hand.

Jun was just staring at the girl, feeling in love and he thought 'She looks more beautiful'

Days passed, they spend their time together. Laying under the lights that looks like a stars. Walking side by side on a road. Laughing like there's no problem at all. Holding a lantern and was ready to let it go.

But then,

His order came. "Sir, this is your order. One cappuccino and a chocolate, Enjoy your stay!" 

Jun lowered his head, he looks at his hand. The drawing was not there also the girl. It was just him and his imagination.

Jun ate and drank his order. He finished the drawing of the girl in his dream. 

'I hope to see you, my star.'

--

Hope you liked it, tho it sucks but dang! Jun is jwgdubwh, he's almost perfect! Sorry for my grammatically errors

author: @uniheatherr
text:
Here's a rough translation of the lyrics, I tried my best to make it as close to the song's original meaning as possible, but there may still be inaccuracies! 

Rainclouds blend out wordlessly
The love that wasn't said
You're the departure, I'm the future 
After a few years in a slump 
My heart is suddenly fine 
You're not here 

At the Silent Boarding Gate 
I watch clouds fly, sky orange and grey
Wanting to fly to the next me 
Shivering from the cold, I pull my collar close, unable to land 
Two parallel universes, no communication 
At the Boarding Gate 
Where should i go, not fully freed yet
There's a path but no will to go
How long does it take, for someone to say, I'm fine 

What happened next, take a guess 
Loneliness led to a long-gone disaster 
I deserved it 

At the Silent Boarding Gate 
I don't see the clouds move, I surrender,  half-awake 
I'm not the one waiting to fly 
With tears inside me, after I knew, even if I land 
In two parallel universes 
At the Boarding Gate
Where should I go, not fully freed yet
There's a path but no will to go
How long does it take, for someone to say, I'm fine 
-END-

author: @caratlove4107
text:
I love 1:25 so much, the way the lighting portrayed only the woman’s face instead of Jun’s. To me, it meant that she was Junhui’s light, and the Chinese lantern and lights solidified it. He was so content at just being there, focusing solely on her. And when she’s gone, he plays with those same pieces of lighting apparatus, thinking about her. 

As someone who went through a sort of breakup literally two days ago, it... I’m reminiscing over the good parts of my relationship. She ignored me up until earlier to text happy birthday and asked me to stay away for now. It’s bittersweet, because we were dysfunctional as all hell, I basically fed her escapism and abandonment issues in a sense. I wish we could’ve stayed friends rather than loosing her like this, so this honestly just- It hit different, alright-

author: @simpingforgyu
text: Junhui, this was so beautiful. Your voice is so soothing, so calming. I absolutely adore the color scheme of the mv, and the way that the sun is almost always setting while you are reminiscing, while never completely going away until the one or two night scenes. We are in the between with you, constantly waiting, not sure what to do. The night scenes with the woman makes me think at that point, there is a comfort knowing that she will be there the next day. It also just ties to the moon and stars and how they are always there, just to disappear, but eventually they come back. But in this mv, that’s not necessarily true, and we see that in the way the moon hovers in the sky as a ghost of a memory. Lmao, or maybe this is me over reading things (I’ve also just woken up.) regardless, thank you for gifting us this beautiful song and mv for carat’s birthday!

author: @stillthewaves
text:
edit: im not really the type to comment here but i just want to share my interpretation of this song.

firstly as the title says, "silent boarding gate", he might be sending off 'something' that other people probably don't know.
in this case, that something could be memories he shared with the girl. letting go something that's been holding him back. the girl could either be a figment of his imagination from his daily routine (or a deja vu) or now just a part of his memory that he's reminiscing at the field(?). the lantern can be a metaphor too to that something that he needs or wants to let go in order to move forward. 

whatever's the real meaning or interpretation behind this, i am so proud of his acting and singing. i hope to see him act one day and hear more of his songs! 加油，文俊辉 💛

author: @tkfc0827
text:
The lyrics are so beautiful so I wanted to try to translate them into English:

Dark clouds fading away
乌云无语晕开
The love that was not said at that time
当时没说的爱
You left, I stand alone in the future
你是离开 我是未来
After years of grief
经历几年的坏
My heart is healed
心也猛然好了起来
But you are not here anymore
你不在

Standing at the boarding gate ”The Loneliness“
在寂寞号登机口
I glance clouds fly away
我瞧云飞走
Sky of half orange and half grey
半橘半灰的天空
Want to fly to the next me
想飞往下一个我
Shivering with cold 
冷的发抖
I pull my sleeves tighter
我拉紧领口
Unable to land
没法降落
There is no contact between two different zones
两个时空 不联络


At the boarding gate
登机门口
Where should I go?
我何去何从？
I am the one who is half-remembered and half-forgotten
半念半忘的是我
There is a way but I don't care to go
有路但没有心走
How long does it take for a person to say "I'm fine"
人得多久 能说 “我好了”

What happens after that? Guess
后来怎样？ 你猜
Loneliness ignite a long-awaited disaster
孤独引燃久违的灾
And I ask for it
我活该

Standing at the boarding gate ”The Loneliness“
在寂寞号登机口
I saw that the clouds were not gone
我瞧云没走
Half-asleep and half-awake, I confess
半梦半醒 我自首
The one waiting to fly is not me
等飞的并不是我
Tears fill my heart
泪在心中

author: @irokimaori6426
text:
I remember, I first heard of Jun in a Chinese reality show for singers. I didn't even know he was part of Seventeen, till he showed up with The8(I wasn't a hardcore fan so I didn't know all of the members, but I liked Seventeen's songs back then)
But in that show, Jun became partners with Yanan of Pentagon... But the latter had to eventually withdraw because of personal reasons.
That time I admired Jun so much. He had stage fright. He couldn't perform alone on the stage. Even Minghao knew and was worried because Yanan took a leave and probably wouldn't get to perform.
Jun was so brave. He kept saying he will wait for Yanan, and if he had to perform alone, he d do his best so Yanan and him won't be eliminated... He did so well.
And when time came that Yanan confirmed to withdraw, Jun declared withdrawal to the show, but insisted on performing his piece because he didn't want the efforts spent by the instrument teacher to be put to waste. Even if the performance wouldn't be part of the competition he insisted on performing it, even if he was nervous and scared that he will have to perform alone..
That was the day I said to myself I loved this boy. That he deserves to be appreciated. I stan talent, but most of all I stan the right attitude. And that attitude is Jun, for me. 
😭😭😭😭😭😭 We don't deserve this boy... He really has grown up right before our very eyes... ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️

author: @je2742
text:
Silent boarding gate -- jun
(It's my first time doing a translation😬）
As the dark clouds left silently
My love haven’t been spoken out at that time
You are the departure but I am the future

After going through the bad times for years 
My heart has been healed  
But you’re not there

At the silent boarding gate
I saw the clouds floating away
The sky was orange but grey to me
I hope you’ll fly to me the next time
Shivering in cold
I pull my collar tighter
Unable to land down
Both our timelines can never be connected

At the boarding gate
Where could I go and where could I be
The one who wishes to forget but still missing you is me
There’s a way but I no longer have the heart to go on
How long does it takes for people be able to say: “I’m fine now”

How I am doing after this
Can you guess
Loneliness has brought disaster
Serves me right thou

At the silent boarding gate
I saw the clouds still haven’t left
To be dreaming even though I am half awake
I surrender to that
I wasn’t the one who wished to fly but my heart is breaking
I know after
Even when the plane has landed
Our timelines will still be parallel

At the boarding gate
Where could I go and where could I be
The one who wishes to forget but still missing you is me
There’s a way but I no longer have the heart to go on
How long does it takes for people to be able to say: “I’m fine now”



p.s. I tried translating most of the lyrics directly from Chinese so the flow between lines might be strange cuz languages have different flows
There are still some lines I translated using my own interpretation so as to join the lines together better. So my interpretation may differ from yours. But pls don't throw shade at me🥺🥺

author: @imsanji5543
text:
I have two meanings of this girl:
- Carats - we are here for them but actually we're not there, not with them
- His family - he miss them, he know that he should make his dreams come true but he leave them, his parents were not happy when he was leaving, so he asked "how long it take them to say they're fine?"

But if we look closer, this girl could be him, his "self" who is with him everytime and leading him... He once said, that he doesn't want show his weakness, he wants to solve his problems on his own; and he's asking "how long it take them to say "i'm fine", he's not okay with being so far from home, but he need to say "it's fine" because there is his home too and members and carats are his family too.

author: @mirandaeira7309
text:
For non-c-carats:

The clouds wordlessly diffuse 
The love that was not told
You are leaving I am the future
After going through a few years of badness,
My heart suddenly feels better
You're not here

At the silent boarding gate
I watch the clouds fly away, the sky that is half orange and half gray
I want to fly to the next me
It's so cold I'm shivering, I grip my collar, unable to descend from flight
Two spaces and time, no contact
At the boarding gate, where do I come from, where do I go, half reminiscing half forgetting
I have a road to walk but no heart to do so
How long does it take, for someone to say, I'm okay now

What happened after that, you guess
Loneliness lit up the long-gone flames of disaster 
It's my fault

At the silent boarding gate
I see that the clouds have not left, in a half-dream and half-awake state, I turn myself in 
I'm not waiting to take off
With tears in my heart, I know that even if I descend
The two time and spaces are parallel

At the boarding gate, where do I come from and where do I go, half reminiscing half forgetting
I have a road to walk but no heart to do so
How long does it take, for someone to say, I'm okay now



Sorry if there are any errors in the translation

author: @babyzee789
text:
In October 2012, Jun moved to South Korea to undergo training under Pledis Entertainment. From 2013 to 2015, he appeared on Seventeen TV and MBC Seventeen Project: Debut Big Plan as a trainee alongside the other future members of his band. He debuted as a member of Seventeen on May 26, 2015 under the stage name Jun. Their first EP 17 Carat was released three days later.

In 2018, he and group member The8 participated in the Chinese music reality show Chao Yin Zhan Ji (潮音战纪). He won the first solo stage competition on the show with his performance of Wo Ming Bai (我明白), a Chinese cover of Seventeen's Thanks. He wrote the Chinese lyrics for the cover. His solo and collaboration stages on the show have been released on digital music platforms owned by Tencent Music.

author: @leah8404
text:
LYRICS AND PERSONAL THEORY OF THE MEANING:

Leaving without moon or cloud in sight
At that time, you asked whether you are farewell and I am return
Please remember the kindness
When my mind healed abruptly, you were not there anymore

At the silent boarding gate 
I leave, flying leisurely into the far distance,
the skies moving back and forth
I want to fly to the next destination
Cold to the point of shivering, I pull my collar tighter
Unable to land, the two timelines connecting each other
At the boarding gate where I have no idea where to go
I wish the one you forget is me
People who don't walk on the road there for them
How long will it take for them to say "I'm fine"?

After that I once thought 
You who were enduring it silently alone 
to wait for me
Serves me right

At the silent boarding gate, I said with a smile 
that I didn't leave, my quiet and defensive actions mocking me
But it has to be, that I am actually not tired in my heart
I know afterwards, even if I land, the two timelines would be parallel
At the boarding gate where I have no idea where to go
I wish the one you forget is me

People who don't talk on the road that was there for them
How long will it take for them to say "I'm fine"?


can we talk about how well thought the entire concept and storyline is? while writing the lyrics down, it made me think so much to point where i started sobbing. i like how it doesn't really show us how or what happened or how the story really ends, but the lyrics and music video give and show us the meaning and how it feels like to be at a silent boarding gate. i PERSONALLY think silent boarding gate is similar to a parallel universe. jun and the girl met in the parallel universe and he knew they couldn't be together for very long. hence the song being called, 'silent boarding gate'. something like entering a parallel universe, creating memories with her, and leaving on his own with those memories still held very close to him. 
theres a lyric "when my mind healed abruptly, you were not there anymore" i just think jun was allowing himself to heal and be one whole again so he can give her the absolute most and better. but when he was ready to go back, she wasnt there anymore to welcome him. 
everyone talking about how the girl left junhui but i feel like jun left the girl.. like i think he was sure when he comes running back to her, someone was gonna be there and welcome him again with open arms. but there was no one. which gives the name, a silent boarding gate.

jun's silent boarding gate is the PERFECT example, theres beauty in pain. 

- again these are just theories tho ^^

author: @deancastro732
text:
De verdad no sé cómo explicar lo feliz que me haces, tú y todo Seventeen, pero este texto va especialmente dirigido a ti. Aunque sé que es imposible que te llegue, no puedo guardar todo esto.
Eres increíble, eres mi fuerza y admiración. Tienes un talento innegable, cuentas con rap, vocal, baile, visual, material de actor y buen coreógrafo, además de letrista. También tienes una personalidad encantadora, sé que muchos han quedado atrapados al ver tu sonrisita, al verte feliz, inquieto, siendo como tú eres, con buenos y malos momentos que te forman.
Eres demasiado valiente, dejando todo lo que tenías para cumplir tus sueños, y lo lograste, ahora nos tienes.
Gracias por existir, por querernos, por ser ese rayito de sol, de paz, de felicidad. Gracias por todo, Jun. Gracias por darme fuerzas y motivos.

author: @micahthelibra
text:
translation: 

Overcast clouds blur wordlessly
The love I never verbalized at that time 
You are departure, I am the future 
Experiencing a few bad years 
My heart suddenly became well 
You’re not here 
At the boarding gate of loneliness 
I watch the clouds fly away, a sky half grey half orange I want to fly to the next me It’s so cold I shiver, 
I hold my collar close, unable to land 
Two places of time and space that do not communicate At the boarding gate 
Where I decide to go – it is me in half memory, half forgottenness 
There’s a path but not the mind to walk it 
How long until someone can say: ‘I’m okay now’? 
Guess what happened later 
Loneliness sparked a disaster that I had not seen again for a long time It’s what I deserve...
At the boarding gate for loneliness, I see the clouds have not left, in half-dream half-wake, I surrender It is not me that is waiting to fly 
The tears are in the heart, I know that later even if I land 
Two places of space and time in parallel At the boarding gate 
Where I decide to go – it is me in half memory, half forgottenness 
There’s a path but not the mind to walk it 
How long until someone can say: ‘I’m okay now’? 
Credits to: @gyuaena...

author: @ellamira1167
text:
LYRICS TRANSLATION: (to cry harder) 

Leaving without moon or cloud in sight 
At that time, you asked 
whether you are farewell and I am return 

Please remember the kindess
When my mind healed abruptly, 
you were not there anymore
 
At the silent boarding gate
I leave, flying leisurely into the far distance,
the skies moving back and forth
I want to fly to the next destination 

Cold to the point of shivering,
I pull my collar tighter
Unable to land, the two timelines connecting each other

At the boarding gate where
I have no idea where to go 
I wish the one you forget is me 

People who don’t walk on the road that was there for them
 How long will it take for them to say “I’m fine”? 

After that I once thought 
You who were enduring it silently alone just to wait for me 
Serves me right 

At the silent boarding gate,
I said with a smile that I didn’t leave, my quiet and defensive actions mocking me 

But it has to be, that I am actually not tired in my heart 
I know afterwards, even if I land, 
the two timelines would be parallel 

At the boarding gate where I have no idea where to go 
I wish the one you forget is me 

People who don’t walk on the road that was there for them
How long will it take for them to say “I’m fine”? 

Credits to: @csvtnogomi , early translation ...
